<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861209-0136 </DOCNO><HL> Standard Oil Forms a UnitTo Handle Firm's Finances</HL><DD> 12/09/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SRD </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard Oil Co. said it formed a unit, Standard Oil Finance, to manage its financial affairs as a profit center.    The unit will handle the day-to-day management of Standard Oil's central finances and provide a range of specialized financial and banking services to the company and its operating units.    Standard Oil Finance will be expected to generate a profit, particularly from trading in the foreign exchange and fixed-income securities markets, said E. John P. Browne, Standard Oil's executive vice president and chief financial officer. Edward P. Campbell, vice president, finance, will head the unit. </TEXT></DOC>